<br>
BUT.<br>
<br>
It's SNOW!  What are some of your favorite snow-stories, be they &quot;first snow of the year&quot; or otherwise?<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, it snowed here today.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slaadya>Slaadya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/02 7:47:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SNOW!  /dance</span><hr size=1> So, I worked at a pair of wineries for a few years.  These establishments are situated along the shores of Lake Erie in Pennsylvania.  So, I am keeping shop one evening...<br>
<br>
...wait, I forgot to tell you how earlier in the day the water boiler had exploded and the hot water heater developed a big leak and I called the boss who came down after I got them shut off and called him and TOOK THE SNOW SHOVEL HOME...<br>
<br>
... so I sit with the limited heat of a 9x6 (inches folks) electric space heater in a small office.  With no windows I had little idea that a storm had come up...<br>
<br>
...and so, with temperatures of 33 below 0 (that is with the windchill) around 8 inches fell AND FROZE TO THE DOORS!!!  I was effectively trapped.<br>
<br>
Long story short... my brother and mother came to the rescue.  I went through two bottles of wine while they worked and took a couple home for each of them.  Wrote a note to the boss that it was payment for cleaning driveway.<br>
<br>
PoSla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lethecerulre>Lethe Cerulre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Siokitty Silvermoon <br>Krazy Kitty</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/02 9:12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SNOW!  /dance</span><hr size=1> This is my favorite snow story.<br>
<br>
I was about 11 and the night before they were forcasting this big, bad blizzard to roll into our area.  This was outside Philly like '91 or so.  So everyone freaked out and went and bought out the stores and they closed schools that evening.  Well... we woke up expecting to see snow... well... there wasn't any..<br>
<br>
I think that day it got to somewhere around 70... could have been a little lower... just thought it was funny that we had this supposed blizzard coming in and it was a nice day instead.<br>
<br>
Another snow story...<br>
<br>
I was born in November... one day my parents were taking a walk and had me in a baby carrying case.  My dad was swinging it to keep me happy and then all the sudden the carrying case felt extra light.  I had fell into the snow with all my blankets and was sitting there quite content.<br>
<br>
PoSiokitty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mystikatfv>MystikatFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/24/02 3:32:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SNOW!  /dance</span><hr size=1> I remember driving about a hundred miles, at night, in the middle of the &quot;Superstorm&quot; of March '93. Quite an adventure, that.<br>
<br>
Taught me to watch the weather before embarking on a road trip. Then again, no one expected that storm to wind up quite as fast as it did, as far south as it did.<br>
<br>
